Map legend :

1 : BAT
2 : WEREWOLF
3 : PANTHER


Bats are kinda slow-paced, but requires you to either (precisely) jump or crouch to dodge them.
Werewolfs are medium-paced, requires you to jump over them.
Panthers are fast-paced, requires you to jump in advance to let them run under you.

One character (and space)'s separation between eachother roughly equals to half the size of the window.
I highly suggest that you put a little bit of space right at the start :).

There you go, you got all the ingredients to make a super cool map !




Also, the first map is hard, but doable ;).